n Career College                   888-560-4222      Vocational Nursing (LVN) Program Accredited, Hands-On Training Scholarships & Financial Aid available for those who qualify.   REQUEST INFORMATION           Select CampusOrange CountyLos AngelesOntarioLynwood                      Select HS Grad Date20172016201520142013201220112010200920082007200620052004200320022001200019991998199719961995199419931992199119901989198819871986198519841983198219811980Pre 1980Haven't Graduated       By clicking below, I consent to receive calls and/or text messages* by a college representative with information for educational opportunities at the number(s) provided above. I understand calls may be initiated by an automated telephone dialing system. I need not grant this consent to receive information or to be eligible to enroll with ACC. (*Standard rates may apply.)           LVN students cultivate the knowledge and skills necessary to provide direct patient care, assessment, diagnostic measurements, procedures and treatments. The combined academic and clinical training prepares vocational nursing students to take the NCLEX-PN for licensure as a practical/vocational nurse. The training program is divided into 4 modules approximately 13 weeks in length (20 weeks for evening/weekend). Each module is comprised of prescribed units of study that build upon each other. Completion of the Vocational Nursing program is acknowledged by the awarding of a diploma.  Train to become a Vocational Nurse at ACC. Request More Information today! ACC cannot guarantee employment       888-560-4222      For graduation rates, median debt of graduates completing these programs and other important information, click here.           Medical Assistant Program | American Career College                   888-560-4222      Medical Assistant Program Accredited, Hands-On Training Scholarships & Financial Aid available for those who qualify.   REQUEST INFORMATION           Select CampusOrange CountyLong BeachLos AngelesOntarioLynwood                      Select HS Grad Date20172016201520142013201220112010200920082007200620052004200320022001200019991998199719961995199419931992199119901989198819871986198519841983198219811980Pre 1980Haven't Graduated       By clicking below, I consent to receive calls and/or text messages* by a college representative with information for educational opportunities at the number(s) provided above. I understand calls may be initiated by an automated telephone dialing system. I need not grant this consent to receive information or to be eligible to enroll with ACC. (*Standard rates may apply.)           Medical Assistants are an important part of the health care team and their responsibilities continue to expand. The MA program provides students with the knowledge and skills necessary to work successfully as a team member in a medical office, clinic, HMO or other health care setting. MA students develop knowledge and skills in administrative and clinical procedures. Competency in preparation of patients for exams, back-office clinical procedures, administration of medications, and routine lab procedures is coupled with a thorough knowledge of the front-office skills necessary to function as part of an efficient medical office.   Train to become a Medical Assistant at ACC. Request More Information today! ACC cannot guarantee employment       888-560-4222      For graduation rates, median debt of graduates completing these programs and other important information, click here.           Medical Billing and Coding Program | American Career College                   888-560-4222      Medical Billing & Coding Program Accredited, Hands-On Training Scholarships & Financial Aid available for those who qualify.   REQUEST INFORMATION           Select CampusOrange CountyLong BeachLos AngelesOntarioLynwood                      Select HS Grad Date20172016201520142013201220112010200920082007200620052004200320022001200019991998199719961995199419931992199119901989198819871986198519841983198219811980Pre 1980Haven't Graduated       By clicking below, I consent to receive calls and/or text messages* by a college representative with information for educational opportunities at the number(s) provided above. I understand calls may be initiated by an automated telephone dialing system. I need not grant this consent to receive information or to be eligible to enroll with ACC. (*Standard rates may apply.)           According to the California Employment Development Department, jobs in medical billing and coding are expected to increase by 19.6% between 2014 and 2024. Prepare for a career in this growing field with training from ACC! The ACC Medical Billing and Coding program is designed to help you learn how to use databases, industry software and various reference materials as you train for the critical responsibility of quickly and accurately recording and reporting patient information. In this program, students will develop their knowledge and skills within a blended model of education. Preparing students for the real life experience of health care data delivery systems, students will engage in on-line learning, as well as lab and computer software applications. In addition, your MBC externship provides a unique opportunity to gain valuable experience in the field and alongside working professionals, preparing you for a successful transition to your career. Accelerated Learning. Want to fast-track your career in Medical Billing & Coding? This program offers an accelerated option to earn your diploma in about 9 months. Request More Information today! ACC cannot guarantee employment       888-560-4222      For graduation rates, median debt of graduates completing these programs and other important information, click here.           Pharmacy Technician Program | American Career College                   888-560-4222      Pharmacy Technician Program Accredited, Hands-On Training Scholarships & Financial Aid available for those who qualify.   REQUEST INFORMATION           Select CampusOrange CountyLos AngelesOntario                      Select HS Grad Date20172016201520142013201220112010200920082007200620052004200320022001200019991998199719961995199419931992199119901989198819871986198519841983198219811980Pre 1980Haven't Graduated       By clicking below, I consent to receive calls and/or text messages* by a college representative with information for educational opportunities at the number(s) provided above. I understand calls may be initiated by an automated telephone dialing system. I need not grant this consent to receive information or to be eligible to enroll with ACC. (*Standard rates may apply.)           According to the California Employment Development Department, jobs for Pharmacy Technicians are expected to increase by 11.6% between 2014 and 2024. Get the education required to enter this growing field with training from ACC! At ACC, our Pharmacy Technician diploma program focuses on preparing you with the technical knowledge and practical skills necessary for positions related to the manufacturing, distribution, or support of pharmacy products. Pharmacy Technician students learn pharmacy law, basic chemistry, pharmacology, dosage calculations, inpatient pharmacy procedures, and retail pharmacy procedures. ACC's dynamic curriculum also prepares you for the professional world by providing training in basic computer operations, such as data input procedures used in maintaining patients' medication records. Accelerated Learning. Want to fast-track your career as a Pharmacy Technician? ACC offers an accelerated option to earn your diploma in about 9 months. Request More Information today! ACC cannot guarantee employment       888-560-4222      For graduation rates, median debt of graduates completing these programs and other important information, click here.     

